The ANC held a media briefing to outline the outcomes of its three-day Lekgotla. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG – The ANC outlined the outcomes of its three-day NEC Lekgotla. The governing party gave some insights into decisions made during their NEC Lekgotla. READ: Respect leadership, Magashule warns members Much media attention has been focused on the party’s integrity commission's findings. Media weekend reports suggested that the commission has called on 23 ANC leaders to step down.